args: Got it. I'll take care of the Mukuroshu\nbefore they move their base.
If you insist on coming, knock yourself\noutâ€”but don't expect me to watch your\nback for even a second.
Now just a corn-shuckin' minute!\nThat ain't no way to talk to me\nwhat after everything I just did!
The only reason ya even know where that\ndarn base IS is 'cause I went'n found it!
So I reckon ya could at least PRETEND\nto be gratefu... Huh? Where'd he go?
Dangnabbit, he's gone and left me!\nLord Seimei, waaaaait!
So that's their base, eh? I hope you\nremembered to bring your jufu.
'Course I did! Heck, I went'n brought,\nuh, one...two...three...49 of 'em!
You know 49 is an unlucky number, right?\nAnyway, to business. How many of them\nare waiting for us inside?
I only followed the one, so there's at\nleast that many! Could be more, though.
So a number equal to or greater than one?\n*sigh* I'll just go look for myself.
O that which can see beyond the horizon!\nI beseech you, reveal our foes!\nOnmyo! Haaaah!
Seeing how many people are in there.\nI count five, though that likely includes\nthe woman you said they kidnapped.
So we only gotta take out four of 'em?\nHeck, this'll be easier than shovin' a\nmuddy hog down a chute!
Back me up, master! I got this!
What are you...?! Ugh. Fine.\nSuit yourself, you stupid fox.
The jig's up, friends! Put them paws in the\nair and don't gimme no backtalk 'bout it!
(I see three of 'em and the one victim.\nReckon that means the other kidnapper's\nsomewhere further inside.)
Well, well. If it isn't Seimei's little dog\ncome to us like a lamb to slaughter.
I ain't a dog OR a lamb! I'm a cute ol' fox!
I'm yer dang rescue party! Now stand back\nwhile I give these fools a thrashin'!
Well, heck! They look all weak and spindly,\nbut they're faster'n greased geese!
Heh. If a shikigami like you is the best\nSeimei can do, it's clear the rumors of\nhis greatness have been exaggerated.
Seimei is no match for our great\nMaster Doman!
They went and got a shikigami!
And no ordinary shikigamiâ€”this one was\ngranted to us by Master Doman,\nand is unparalleled in strength!
That's a darn dirty trick what to keep\ncrammed up yer sleeves!
You can regret your foolishness\nin the depths of hell. Destroy her!
Now do you see why I told you not to run\noff alone, you useless fox?
You protect the womanâ€”I'll take care\nof this rabble here.

We've been waiting for you, Seimei.
Master Doman won't even need to
sully his hands, because we'll finish
you off ourselves!
Hmph. You're going to need greater\nnumbers than that to finish me.
You can't handle this many on your own!
One weakling or a thousand,\nyou're still mere weaklings, moron.
Hoo-eee! Pretty as a picture, Lord Seimei!\nBut now I'm gonna back ya up with this\nhere onmyodo of m'own!
O that which shines like the darn sun!\nI beseech ya, release yer light'n makeâ€”
Argh! When did YOU sneak up behind me?!
Surrender, or it's the end\nfor this little lady here.
It's all my dang fault. If I'd just been\nwatchin' her like ya told me to...
Heck no! I ain't gonna just run and leave\nya what to deal with all them folk alone!
Well, you're not helping me by being here,\nyou stupid fox!
Shikigami Kuzunoha, I order you to scatter\nthe jufu you possess and flee our foes!\nOnmyo!
Argh! My body's movin' all on its own!\nDon't do it, Lord Seimei! I don't wanna\nbe runnin' away without ya!
Go find something even a useless idiot\nlike you can doâ€”I'm counting on you.
Thought I told you not to move.
You told ME not to move, but I don't think\nanyone mentioned it to my stupid fox.
You think you're so smart, don't you?
*pant* *pant* I can finally move\non my own again...
(I gotta get back to Lord Seimei! It's all\nmy fault, so I gotta be the one what\nmakes everything right again!)
